Hereâ€™s a simple explanation:
ðŸ”¹ Linear Probing:
If a collision occurs, check the next slot (index + 1, then +2, and so on).
Keep moving one step ahead until an empty slot is found.
Example:
If hash index is 3 and itâ€™s full, try 4 â†’ 5 â†’ 6...
ðŸ”¹ Quadratic Probing:
If a collision occurs, check slots using square increments (index + 1Â², +2Â², +3Â²...).
This spreads out the checks more widely.
Example:
If hash index is 3 and itâ€™s full, try 4 (3+1Â²) â†’ 7 (3+2Â²) â†’ 2 (3+3Â² % 10)...
âš ï¸ Difference:
Feature	Linear Probing	Quadratic ProbingStep pattern	+1, +2, +3...	+1Â², +2Â², +3Â²...
Clustering	More (primary)	Less (secondary)
Simplicity	Easy	Slightly complex
